{"session_id":"019f63ce-9b25-75d1-a814-0d64a06ce805","turn_id":"019f63ce-a3fa-7e92-9c13-9591fdd6f9a2","transcript_path":null,"cwd":"/Users/lawrence/fun/cmuxterm-hq/worktrees/feat-simulator-pane","hook_event_name":"Stop","model":"gpt-5.6-sol","permission_mode":"bypassPermissions","stop_hook_active":false,"last_assistant_message":"{\"findings\":[{\"title\":\"Do not permanently tear down a temporarily detached simulator view\",\"body\":\"`viewWillMove(toWindow:)` treats every transition from a window to `nil` as final destruction and calls `teardown()`. AppKit/SwiftUI can temporarily detach and later reuse the same `NSView` during workspace, split, or canvas reparenting. Because teardown permanently sets `isTornDown`, subsequent `update()` calls cannot recreate the frame source, display link, or input callbacks, leaving the reused simulator pane black and inert. Final teardown should be owned by the representable lifetime/dismantle path rather than a transient window detachment.\",\"priority\":\"P1\",\"confidence\":0.91,\"category\":\"regression\",\"code_location\":{\"file_path\":\"Packages/macOS/CmuxSimulator/Sources/CmuxSimulatorUI/Views/SimulatorRemoteSurfaceView.swift\",\"line\":182}},{\"title\":\"Replace the new Combine-backed canvas presentation model\",\"body\":\"This introduces a new `ObservableObject`/`@Published` change-propagation model for every canvas-hosted panel. The repository's concurrency architecture explicitly requires new propagation to use Observation (`@Observable`) or an async sequence and avoid adding Combine/`ObservableObject`. Keeping this bridge creates another broad SwiftUI invalidation and lifecycle mechanism in a pane-hosting path; make the presentation model `@Observable` and consume it through Observation instead.\",\"priority\":\"P2\",\"confidence\":0.98,\"category\":\"maintainability\",\"code_location\":{\"file_path\":\"Sources/Canvas/CanvasPaneContent.swift\",\"line\":21}}],\"overall_correctness\":\"patch is incorrect\",\"overall_explanation\":\"The simulator view can be irreversibly torn down during ordinary temporary AppKit detachment, which can leave a reused pane nonfunctional. The change also introduces a new Combine observation bridge contrary to the repository's required concurrency architecture.\",\"overall_confidence\":0.91}"}